abstract: The story behind the first part of our new series on presidential candidates.
snippet: The story behind the first part of our new series on presidential candidates.
lead_paragraph: Today’s episode kicks off “The Candidates,” a new series from “The Daily” that profiles the four top-polling Democratic presidential contenders: Pete Buttigieg, Bernie Sanders, Elizabeth Warren and Joe Biden. Producers Clare Toeniskoetter and Luke Vander Ploeg told us about how they approached the first episode:

abstract: Many of the existential questions gripping the Democratic Party center on one mysterious figure: the “moderate” voter.

abstract: Mr. Obama, in his latest remarks about the Democratic primary race, said the party should focus less on differences among the candidates and more on defeating President Trump.
snippet: Mr. Obama, in his latest remarks about the Democratic primary race, said the party should focus less on differences among the candidates and more on defeating President Trump.
lead_paragraph: LOS ALTOS HILLS, Calif. — Former President Barack Obama urged Democrats on Thursday to “chill out” about the party’s 2020 field and to avoid putting candidates through “purity tests,” and warned that average voters were “nervous about changes that might take away what little they have.”
